title: Compiler unexpectedly panicked

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
I switched branches (to a branch that ordinarily compiles fine), ran `cargo run`, and saw the error below.  It looks like the issue happened while trying to compile Diesel.  Rerunning `cargo run` reproduced the error, but `cargo clean` fixed it.  Sorry I don't have a small sample program to share that would reproduce the issue.
